By Lanre Adesanya
The Speaker of the Lagos State House of Assembly,  Rt. Hon. Mudashiru Obasa, has called on Nigerians not to relent in sharing love and ensure  unity and pecaeful co-existence among themselves .
Rt. Hon. Obasa made this assertion  in his Sallah message through a statement signed by his Chief Press Secretary, Musbau Razak.
The Lagos Assembly Speaker also urged Nigerians to be vigilant at all times and cooperate with the government at all levels to fight crimes in the society.
“Ramadan teaches us love and unity, I urge us not to relent in sharing the love and unity like we have done during the fasting period. We should continue to spread love and co-habit peacefully. This is the essence of Ramadan which we must not neglect,” Rt. Hon. Obasa said.
ALSO SEE: What Buhari told Nigerians on sallah day
The Lagos Assembly Speaker also urged Nigerians to remain vigilant at all times so that they will assist government at all levels in combating crimes.
“The issue of security is a collective task involving the governed and the government. So we must be vigilant at all times. We must be able to provide information on any questionable individual or group in our communities to security agents. This assist government in nipping crime at the bud,” he advised.
The Lagos Assembly Speaker also asssured Nigerians that the All Progressives Congress (APC) at all levels is committed to improving their lives and enhancing their welfare.
